    c. a judicial decision in the Licensor’s jurisdiction which has a material adverse effect on his/her ability to not comply with this Public License.
This termination shall be effective two (2) months after the effective date of the event that gave rise to such termination. In such event, all licenses granted under this Public License shall be terminated. This termination right shall supplement, and not replace, any other termination right that the Licensor may have, now or in the future.

8.2. In the event of any termination of this Public License for any reason:

    a. the Licensor shall offer, if possible, any future grant for the Public License without terminating his/her Initial Offer as set forth in Section 8(a); and

    b. the Licensor’s previous offer of the Work under the terms of this Public License shall remain terminated subject to the passage of time, so that, if the condition precedent to such termination is removed, the termination is lifted and the Licensor’s offer for the Work is reinstated.
For the avoidance of doubt, the expiry or termination of this Public License shall not affect any right, duty or liability incurred or accrued prior to the date of expiry or termination.

